            <title>[FELIX-3054] PathInfo &amp; ServletPath</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3054</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is an bizarre choice with the splitting between PathInfo, ServletPath and ContextPath.&lt;br/&gt;
Indeed when i register a servlet (or a resource) to the path &quot;/path1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
In my HttpContext when i receive a request (in handleSecurity for example) the information associated with the request(/path1/abcd) are the following:&lt;br/&gt;
PathInfo: /path1/abcd&lt;br/&gt;
ServletPath: &lt;br/&gt;
ContextPath: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t  a weird behaviour? &lt;br/&gt;
A splitting like the following one, isn&apos;t it more logical?&lt;br/&gt;
PathInfo: /abcd&lt;br/&gt;
ServletPath: /path1&lt;br/&gt;
ContextPath: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
